attendance /əˈtɛndəns/

(attendances) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Someone's attendance at an event or an institution is the fact that they are present at the event or go regularly to the institution. 出勤; 出席 

例： Her attendance in school was sporadic. 她在学校的出勤率很低。 

2. N-VAR The attendance at an event is the number of people who are present at it. 出席人数 

例： Rain played a big part in the air show's drop in attendance. 下雨是这次飞行表演观众数量下降的主要原因。

